INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2014-08-28 10:55:12','2014-08-28 10:55:12','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2014-08-29 06:46:41','2014-08-29 06:46:41','',0,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2014-08-28 10:55:12','2014-08-28 10:55:12','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2014-08-28 10:55:12','2014-08-28 10:55:12','',0,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2014-08-28 11:16:45','2014-08-28 11:16:45','','logo','','inherit','open','open','','logo','','','2014-08-28 11:16:45','2014-08-28 11:16:45','',0,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/logo.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(5,1,'2014-08-28 11:36:44','2014-08-28 11:36:44','Under Construction','Testing','','trash','closed','closed','','testing','','','2014-08-29 06:46:39','2014-08-29 06:46:39','',0,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=5',0,'post','',0),(6,1,'2014-08-28 11:36:44','2014-08-28 11:36:44','Under Construction','Testing','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2014-08-28 11:36:44','2014-08-28 11:36:44','',5,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=6',0,'revision','',0),(7,1,'2014-08-28 11:42:55','2014-08-28 11:42:55','After two years in development, Ghost, Gervasoni’s most successful casual relaxed furniture collection, has now been realized for outdoor use. First available products include a collection of sofas &amp; armchairs, with customization available for dining chairs and a sectional system. For the first time, hospitality contract and residential designers can choose to ignore the commercial aluminum and plastics systems that have dominated the outdoor furniture market in recent years.\r\n\r\nVisually identical to the indoor collection, Ghost for outdoor seating is modern, comfortable, and as attractive as its indoor counterpart. Once again, Gervasoni leads the casual relaxed furniture market!\r\n\r\nGhost is available with waterproof foam and fabrics, Classification 117 foam (fire resistance) and can be specified with COM\r\n\r\nDesigned by Paola Navone, first introduced at the Salone del Mobile in 2007, Ghost quickly became Gervasoni’s most important upholstery collection. Much specified by designers for its cameleon nature, disappearing under the exterior of the fabric choice. The interior collection has gradually expanded to now include multiple varaitions of armchairs, dining chairs, sectional systems, ottomans (floor and back rest), love seats,  sofas. Beds are also available in variations of style and size, including a sofa and trundle bed.\r\n\r\nGervasoni Ghost is in use worldwide in upscale hospitality contract and residential locations and has been specified by many of the world’s top interior design firms.\r\n\r\nSee a few Ghost installations here:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html</a>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About Gervasoni</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Founded in 1882, the company is currently managed by Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni - third generation family members.</p?\r\n\r\n<p>While aesthetic standards and production techniques have changed over the years, the company’s passion for beauty and artisan production has not. Modernity, comfort, the desire to create unique living spaces, attention to detail and artisan production and use of natural materials are hallmarks of Gervasoni products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company designs, develops, manufactures and markets furniture solutions for the home and for the hospitality contract sector in its production facility of 30000 sq. m in Pavia di Udine. The company employs 80 people many of whom are third generation. Collaboration with some of the most qualified designers such as Paola Navone – artistic director of the company – Marco Piva, Michael Sodeau and Jasper Startup, guarantees aesthetic quality and the continued experimentation with new materials.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following the family\'s entrepreneurial vocation, in 2009 Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni acquired IFA srl – a company specialized in the production of high quality wooden chairs – launching the brand Very Wood specifically for the hospitality contract market. And in 2012, Gervasoni presented Letti&amp;co., its new brand dedicated to the culture of sleep and born from collaboration with Paola Navone, who is also Artistic Director of the new brand.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Sustainability is a commitment that the company pursues in all phases of the production cycle. Commitment to the environment is recognized by several environmental certifications: the Quality certification UNI EN ISO 9001: 2008, the Environmental Management Certification UNI EN ISO 14001: 2004, the Certification for the Management of Workers \' Health and Safety OHSAS 18001: 2012.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Gervasoni collections are currently distributed in more than fifty countries worldwide. 65% of the turnover is export.</p>\r\n\r\nFor further information, images or prices contact North American Agent, imoderni llc, 2750 NW 3<sup>rd</sup> Ave, Miami FL 33127. 305.865.8577. <a href=\"mailto:info@imoderni.com\">info@imoderni.com</a>','For the First Time, Indoor Comfort Outdoors!','','publish','open','closed','','testing-2','','','2014-09-01 05:58:35','2014-09-01 05:58:35','',0,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=7',0,'post','',0),(8,1,'2014-08-28 11:42:55','2014-08-28 11:42:55','Under Construction','Testing','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2014-08-28 11:42:55','2014-08-28 11:42:55','',7,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=8',0,'revision','',0),(9,1,'2014-09-01 05:56:26','2014-09-01 05:56:26','After two years in development, Ghost, Gervasoni’s most successful casual relaxed furniture collection, has now been realized for outdoor use. First available products include a collection of sofas &amp; armchairs, with customization available for dining chairs and a sectional system. For the first time, hospitality contract and residential designers can choose to ignore the commercial aluminum and plastics systems that have dominated the outdoor furniture market in recent years.\n\nVisually identical to the indoor collection, Ghost for outdoor seating is modern, comfortable, and as attractive as its indoor counterpart. Once again, Gervasoni leads the casual relaxed furniture market!\n\nGhost is available with waterproof foam and fabrics, Classification 117 foam (fire resistance) and can be specified with COM\n\nDesigned by Paola Navone, first introduced at the Salone del Mobile in 2007, Ghost quickly became Gervasoni’s most important upholstery collection. Much specified by designers for its cameleon nature, disappearing under the exterior of the fabric choice. The interior collection has gradually expanded to now include multiple varaitions of armchairs, dining chairs, sectional systems, ottomans (floor and back rest), love seats,  sofas. Beds are also available in variations of style and size, including a sofa and trundle bed.\n\nGervasoni Ghost is in use worldwide in upscale hospitality contract and residential locations and has been specified by many of the world’s top interior design firms.\n\nSee a few Ghost installations here:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html</a>\n\n<p><strong>About Gervasoni</strong></p>\n\n<p>Founded in 1882, the company is currently managed by Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni - third generation family members.</p?\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\nWhile aesthetic standards and production techniques have changed over the years, the company’s passion for beauty and artisan production has not. Modernity, comfort, the desire to create unique living spaces, attention to detail and artisan production and use of natural materials are hallmarks of Gervasoni products.\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\nThe company designs, develops, manufactures and markets furniture solutions for the home and for the hospitality contract sector in its production facility of 30000 sq. m in Pavia di Udine. The company employs 80 people many of whom are third generation. Collaboration with some of the most qualified designers such as Paola Navone – artistic director of the company – Marco Piva, Michael Sodeau and Jasper Startup, guarantees aesthetic quality and the continued experimentation with new materials.\n\nFollowing the family\'s entrepreneurial vocation, in 2009 Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni acquired IFA srl – a company specialized in the production of high quality wooden chairs – launching the brand Very Wood specifically for the hospitality contract market. And in 2012, Gervasoni presented Letti&amp;co., its new brand dedicated to the culture of sleep and born from collaboration with Paola Navone, who is also Artistic Director of the new brand.\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\nSustainability is a commitment that the company pursues in all phases of the production cycle. Commitment to the environment is recognized by several environmental certifications: the Quality certification UNI EN ISO 9001: 2008, the Environmental Management Certification UNI EN ISO 14001: 2004, the Certification for the Management of Workers \' Health and Safety OHSAS 18001: 2012.\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\nGervasoni collections are currently distributed in more than fifty countries worldwide. 65% of the turnover is export.\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\nFor further information, images or prices contact North American Agent, imoderni llc, 2750 NW 3<sup>rd</sup> Ave, Miami FL 33127. 305.865.8577. <a href=\"mailto:info@imoderni.com\">info@imoderni.com</a>','For the First Time, Indoor Comfort Outdoors!','','inherit','open','open','','7-autosave-v1','','','2014-09-01 05:56:26','2014-09-01 05:56:26','',7,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=9',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2014-08-28 11:47:37','2014-08-28 11:47:37','','120','','inherit','open','open','','120','','','2014-08-28 11:47:37','2014-08-28 11:47:37','',7,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/120.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(12,1,'2014-08-28 11:47:50','2014-08-28 11:47:50','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-11\" src=\"http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/120-300x162.jpg\" alt=\"120\" width=\"300\" height=\"162\" />After two years in development, Ghost, Gervasoni’s most successful casual relaxed furniture collection, has now been realized for outdoor use. First available products include a collection of sofas &amp; armchairs, with customization available for dining chairs and a sectional system. For the first time, hospitality contract and residential designers can choose to ignore the commercial aluminum and plastics systems that have dominated the outdoor furniture market in recent years. Visually identical to the indoor collection, Ghost for outdoor seating is modern, comfortable, and as attractive as its indoor counterpart. Once again, Gervasoni leads the casual relaxed furniture market!\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nGhost is available with waterproof foam and fabrics, Classification 117 foam (fire resistance) and can be specified with COM\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nDesigned by Paola Navone, first introduced at the Salone del Mobile in 2007, Ghost quickly became Gervasoni’s most important upholstery collection. Much specified by designers for its cameleon nature, disappearing under the exterior of the fabric choice. The interior collection has gradually expanded to now include multiple varaitions of armchairs, dining chairs, sectional systems, ottomans (floor and back rest), love seats,  sofas. Beds are also available in variations of style and size, including a sofa and trundle bed.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nGervasoni Ghost is in use worldwide in upscale hospitality contract and residential locations and has been specified by many of the world’s top interior design firms.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nSee a few Ghost installations here:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html</a>\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\n<strong>About Gervasoni</strong>\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nFounded in 1882, the company is currently managed by Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni - third generation family members.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nWhile aesthetic standards and production techniques have changed over the years, the company’s passion for beauty and artisan production has not. Modernity, comfort, the desire to create unique living spaces, attention to detail and artisan production and use of natural materials are hallmarks of Gervasoni products.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nThe company designs, develops, manufactures and markets furniture solutions for the home and for the hospitality contract sector in its production facility of 30000 sq. m in Pavia di Udine. The company employs 80 people many of whom are third generation. Collaboration with some of the most qualified designers such as Paola Navone – artistic director of the company – Marco Piva, Michael Sodeau and Jasper Startup, guarantees aesthetic quality and the continued experimentation with new materials.\r\n\r\nFollowing the family\'s entrepreneurial vocation, in 2009 Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni acquired IFA srl – a company specialized in the production of high quality wooden chairs – launching the brand Very Wood specifically for the hospitality contract market. And in 2012, Gervasoni presented Letti&amp;co., its new brand dedicated to the culture of sleep and born from collaboration with Paola Navone, who is also Artistic Director of the new brand.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nSustainability is a commitment that the company pursues in all phases of the production cycle. Commitment to the environment is recognized by several environmental certifications: the Quality certification UNI EN ISO 9001: 2008, the Environmental Management Certification UNI EN ISO 14001: 2004, the Certification for the Management of Workers \' Health and Safety OHSAS 18001: 2012.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nGervasoni collections are currently distributed in more than fifty countries worldwide. 65% of the turnover is export.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nFor further information, images or prices contact North American Agent, imoderni llc, 2750 NW 3<sup>rd</sup> Ave, Miami FL 33127. 305.865.8577. <a href=\"mailto:info@imoderni.com\">info@imoderni.com</a>','For the First Time, Indoor Comfort Outdoors!','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2014-08-28 11:47:50','2014-08-28 11:47:50','',7,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=12',0,'revision','',0),(13,1,'2014-08-28 11:48:07','2014-08-28 11:48:07','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-11\" src=\"http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/120-300x162.jpg\" alt=\"120\" width=\"300\" height=\"162\" />After two years in development, Ghost, Gervasoni’s most successful casual relaxed furniture collection, has now been realized for outdoor use. First available products include a collection of sofas &amp; armchairs, with customization available for dining chairs and a sectional system. For the first time, hospitality contract and residential designers can choose to ignore the commercial aluminum and plastics systems that have dominated the outdoor furniture market in recent years.\r\n\r\nVisually identical to the indoor collection, Ghost for outdoor seating is modern, comfortable, and as attractive as its indoor counterpart. Once again, Gervasoni leads the casual relaxed furniture market!\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nGhost is available with waterproof foam and fabrics, Classification 117 foam (fire resistance) and can be specified with COM\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nDesigned by Paola Navone, first introduced at the Salone del Mobile in 2007, Ghost quickly became Gervasoni’s most important upholstery collection. Much specified by designers for its cameleon nature, disappearing under the exterior of the fabric choice. The interior collection has gradually expanded to now include multiple varaitions of armchairs, dining chairs, sectional systems, ottomans (floor and back rest), love seats,  sofas. Beds are also available in variations of style and size, including a sofa and trundle bed.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nGervasoni Ghost is in use worldwide in upscale hospitality contract and residential locations and has been specified by many of the world’s top interior design firms.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nSee a few Ghost installations here:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/comporta.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/conscious-hotel-vondelpark.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/der-schwarzacher.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-mykonos.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/grace-santorini.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/romagnoli.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/la-f%C3%A8line-blanche.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/penthouse-villa.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/vilalara-thalasso-resort.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/sirene-blue-resort.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html\">http://www.gervasonicontract.com/en/design-hotel-europa-monetti.html</a>\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\n<strong>About Gervasoni</strong>\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nFounded in 1882, the company is currently managed by Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni - third generation family members.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nWhile aesthetic standards and production techniques have changed over the years, the company’s passion for beauty and artisan production has not. Modernity, comfort, the desire to create unique living spaces, attention to detail and artisan production and use of natural materials are hallmarks of Gervasoni products.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nThe company designs, develops, manufactures and markets furniture solutions for the home and for the hospitality contract sector in its production facility of 30000 sq. m in Pavia di Udine. The company employs 80 people many of whom are third generation. Collaboration with some of the most qualified designers such as Paola Navone – artistic director of the company – Marco Piva, Michael Sodeau and Jasper Startup, guarantees aesthetic quality and the continued experimentation with new materials.\r\n\r\nFollowing the family\'s entrepreneurial vocation, in 2009 Giovanni and Michele Gervasoni acquired IFA srl – a company specialized in the production of high quality wooden chairs – launching the brand Very Wood specifically for the hospitality contract market. And in 2012, Gervasoni presented Letti&amp;co., its new brand dedicated to the culture of sleep and born from collaboration with Paola Navone, who is also Artistic Director of the new brand.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nSustainability is a commitment that the company pursues in all phases of the production cycle. Commitment to the environment is recognized by several environmental certifications: the Quality certification UNI EN ISO 9001: 2008, the Environmental Management Certification UNI EN ISO 14001: 2004, the Certification for the Management of Workers \' Health and Safety OHSAS 18001: 2012.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nGervasoni collections are currently distributed in more than fifty countries worldwide. 65% of the turnover is export.\r\n<h3 class=\"post-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\"></h3>\r\nFor further information, images or prices contact North American Agent, imoderni llc, 2750 NW 3<sup>rd</sup> Ave, Miami FL 33127. 305.865.8577. <a href=\"mailto:info@imoderni.com\">info@imoderni.com</a>','For the First Time, Indoor Comfort Outdoors!','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2014-08-28 11:48:07','2014-08-28 11:48:07','',7,'http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/?p=13',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2014-08-28 11:49:08','2014-08-28 11:49:08','<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-11 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://dev.tenthmatrix.co.uk:8088/imoderni/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/120-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"120\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />After two years in development, Ghost, Gervasoni’s most successful casual relaxed furniture collection, has now been realized for outdoor use. First available products include a collection of sofas &amp; armchairs, with customization available for dining chairs and a sectional system. For the first time, hospitality contract and residential designers can choose to ignore the commercial aluminum and plastics systems that have dominated the outdoor furniture market in recent years.\r\n\r\nVisually identical to the indoor collection, Ghost for outdoor seating is modern, comfortable, and as attractive as its indoor counterpart. 